#1 Support for single-pane and multi-pane using dynamic and flexible UI fragments
#2 Progress bars to avoid empty screen display during the network downloading
#3 Runtime permissions for devices running on Marshmellow or above
#4 Retaining fragment state to avoid recreation on orientation change
#5 Retorfit library to handle background network operations, enforcing Dependency Injection and abstraction of Model from View
#6 ROOM data persistence library from Google I/O 2017 has been used to back up cloud data into local machine for smooth handling of application in no network situation

